Commentary: full on leg stump, tries to clip it off his pads but misses. Hits his thigh instead. They scamper across for the single
Commentary_short: Southee to Fakhar Zaman, 1 leg bye

Commentary: back of a length outside off, straightens after pitching, tapped off the back foot to cover. No run on offer
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, outswing on offer, and takes the leading edge as he tries to nudge this towards the leg side. Lobs just over point and falls safe
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, 2 runs

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, angling into Shehzad and it's pulled beautifully! Beats midwicket, and races away thereafter. Sat up nicely for the batsman to send this away
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length wide outside off, left alone by Shehzad. Not tempted by this wide ball
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, driven down the ground to mid off
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, prods forward and drives through the line of the ball. Goes past the non-striker's right and beats mid on as well. A simple punch earns him a boundary. Off the mark
Commentary_short: Boult to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle, clipped off his toes towards the man in the deep on the leg side
Commentary_short: Boult to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, big stride forward and driven towards the cover region. Stopped by the infielder
Commentary_short: Boult to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, opens the bat's face and taps it to point. The infielder races in and stops the duo from stealing a single
Commentary_short: Boult to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump and angling across the batsman's body, glanced towards point off the back foot. Just opened the bat's face
Commentary_short: Boult to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, overpitched actually but not a yorker. Allows Shehzad to drive down the ground again, forcing mid off to give it a chase. Stopped in the deep eventually
Commentary_short: Boult to Ahmed Shehzad, 3 runs

Commentary: back of a length outside off, stays tall and punches it off the back foot to cover
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: full outside off, tries to punch off the back foot but it's bottom edged behind the batsman. Comes off the bat's toe end with a big gap between bat and pad
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, tries to pull but plays for the wrong length. Plays over the ball as it goes through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, and it's pulled along the carpet once again! Off the bat's middle and it's racing away to deep midwicket, but a terrific diving effort from Anaru Kitchen in the deep saves two
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, 2 runs

Commentary: terrific! Full and straight, and emphatically driven down the ground for another boundary. Stands tall and trusts the bounce as he hits through it's line. No chance for mid on
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length but too wide outside off, driven square off the front foot and it finds the gap between cover point and point. Races away. Controlled shot, played along the ground, with the bat's open face
Commentary_short: Southee to Ahmed Shehzad, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, cramps Zaman for room. Chopped off the back foot towards point
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump but angling across his body, slapped with minimal footwork past point once again. Got his front foot out of the ball's way and smacked in front of square
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on leg stump, misses the leg-side slog. Inside edges the shot onto his body
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, driven towards cover but comes off the bat's top half. Not hit well enough
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump and angling into the batsman as he charges down the ground. Cramped for space. Tapped towards the leg side
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Ahmed Shehzad, no run

Commentary: there's a noise, but not out says the umpire. New Zealand review for the caught behind. Shehzad walked across to the off side, in an attempt to cheekily paddle this behind on the leg side, but misses the shot. Taken low by the keeper, but did it come off the glove? Yes, it did! There's the first wicket.
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Ahmed Shehzad, OUT
Dismissal_text: Ahmed Shehzad c †Blundell b de Grandhomme 19 (18b 3x4 0x6) SR: 105.55

Commentary: full on middle stump, nudged off the front foot towards the off side
Commentary_short: Boult to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, pulled towards midwicket but not off the meat of the bat. Dribbles away to the fiielder
Commentary_short: Boult to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside off, slashes hard at it and lifts this up and over point. Work for Ish Sodhi at third man, who has to race across the boundary line to intercept
Commentary_short: Boult to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: full on off stump, driven off the front foot but mistimed. To cover once again
Commentary_short: Boult to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, and its pulled by the new batsman towards cow corner. Work for Kitchen in the deep once again, but his sliding stop ensures the ball does not go to the boundary
Commentary_short: Boult to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, and the extra bounce takes it over the batsman's cut shot. Came charging down the ground but the zip off the surface forces him to miss that shot
Commentary_short: Boult to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, stays tall and punches this back to the bowler
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on middle and off, shuffles across to the off side and taps this to mid on. They want a quick single, but none on offer
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, rocks onto his back foot and carves this past point! Muscles it away, taking full advantage of the room offered
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump, gently turned off his toes towards midwicket for a quick run. Loud and early call for the run from Babar
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: short ball on middle and it's pulled! Thwacked so hard and off the sweet spot of the bat that the flat-shot goes for a six. Lands just beyond the ropes at deep backward square. First maximum of the evening
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: good length on middle, the batsman backs away and cuts but can't breach the infield
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: short ball first up, no real spin this time. Gets away with the loose ball. Pulled along the ground off the back foot to the man in the deep on the leg side
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, spins into the left-hander, pulled over midwicket, but the umpire calls it a no ball! Replays suggest that Sodhi's delivery was a completely legal ball. Free hit
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, (no ball) 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, and it's lifted straight. Doesn't have the distance, and it's taken by Southee at long off! But it's not out since the previous delivery was erroneously called a no ball
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, backs away and carves towards point for a single
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, turns away from the batsman. Cut off the back foot, but there's the man at point for that shot
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: tossed up on middle stump, and Fakhar attempts a slog sweep! Misses the shot completely, but very lucky that the ball doesn't break off stump. Didn't pick the wrong'un at all
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, played with soft hands towards short cover for a quick single
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: flat ball first up, on a good length on middle and leg, bunted towards cow corner off the back foot
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, no real spin on offer and it's driven past the bowler's right to mid off
Commentary_short: Santner to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, and the batsman backs away towards the leg side to make some extra room. Slapped past cover point thereafter
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length wide outside off, turned off the back foot with soft hands to midwicket. Nobody there inside the circle, and Babar calls nice and early for the second. Boult's throw in is great though, and forces Babar to dive into his crease
Commentary_short: Santner to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: tossed up full outside off, straightens after pitching. Punched off the back foot to cover
Commentary_short: Santner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: fuller ball but outside off, carved square off the back foot with the bat's open face. But can't go past the infield
Commentary_short: Santner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, legspin. Tries to pull this behind square but mistimed to short fine leg. The batsman's in two minds, and can't play the intended shot
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, backs away towards the leg side and pulls along the ground to deep midwicket once again. Kitchen's been excellent in that region, another sliding effort in the deep limits it to only a single
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up on off stump, and this time he picks the wrong'un up. Got his front foot out of the ball's way and it's smacked over the non-striker's head. No chance for long on to race across
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle and leg, nudged off the back foot to midwicket with soft hands
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: short on off stump but spinning into the batsman, cut square off the back foot and Babar calls for the second once again. Direct hit from Santer in the deep, but Babar was in by then
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: sliced, but straight to point! Earns the wicket by cramping Babar for room. Floater on a good length outside off, and Babar is enticed to cut. Played with the sliced bat, and goes straight to KW. Simple take for the NZ captain
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Babar Azam, OUT
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam c Williamson b Sodhi 18 (17b 1x4 0x6) SR: 105.88

Commentary: good length on leg stump, slower ball too, and the batsman is deceived sligthly. Muscled towards the leg side but the bat turns in his hands. Falls just short of the bowler on his followthrough
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, cramped for room once again but he attempts the cut anyway. Top edged, but falls just short of the diving fielder at short third man. Nice change of pace
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, tries to turn it towards the leg side but through his shot too early. Leading edge towards cover
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off stump, sticks his bat out and pings it down to Sodhi at third man
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: overpitched full on leg stump, eventually a yorker as the batsman walks down the ground. Hits his bat, then his boot, and then lands up near his feet. But the batsman has no idea where the ball is, and he attempts to run. The bowler notices, and races down the wicket and kicks the ball onto the stumps. But the batsman was in by then
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full toss outside off, and met by the batsman while charging down. Slapped while shimming towards the bowler, and beats mid off. Sends the loose ball away
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length just outside off, straighter one, cut to point. Misfield from the fielder as he dives across backward point, and the finger touch takes it beyond Boult. Chase for both fielders
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Sarfraz Ahmed, 3 runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, muscles his pull along the ground to midwicket
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, and it's swept off the front foot to deep midwicket. Sarfraz slips and is in splits while playing that shot. Ouch
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: floated outside off, and Zaman takes Sodhi on! Smacked so hard down the ground, and despite it being in the air, the bowler goes for self-preservation. Gets out of the ball's way just in time
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle stump, turned off his hips to midwicket and Sarfraz strugges to complete the run.
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length just outside off stump, spins slightly away from the batsman. Misses the cut, and sharply taken by the keeper
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: full outside leg stump after seeing the batsman back away to the leg side. Bunted down the ground to long on
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside off, this time it's swept to deep backward square but played rather tentatively. Waited for the ball this time instead of reaching at it
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside leg stump. Fakhar, though, was premeditated. Plays a reverse sweep towards the left-hander's off side
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, and that's lifted beautifully over cover. Driven inside out, and beats both wide long off and deep extra cover. Neither fielder can stop that
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: awkwardly played! Full on middle stump, and Sarfraz almost yorks himself. Swept, but too fine. Straight to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: full outside off stump, and smacked with the spin once again towards deep extra cover. Floaty ball, and the batsman waited for it, before lifting it over the infield. Ends the over with a boundary
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, comes down the wicket and slapped to cover. They're racing across for the quick single. Dangerous, but CDG misses the direct hit at the non-striker's. Oh dear, overthrows, with no one backing up
Commentary_short: Southee to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, muscled off the back foot to deep midwicket once again. Not timed well enough, which fortunately for the batting team, allows them to take the second run as well
Commentary_short: Southee to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs

Commentary: short on leg stump, and the tall batsman ducks out of the ball's line. One for the over, says the umpire
Commentary_short: Southee to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, tries to slog this towards the leg side but can't get the connection. Played from near the bat's sticker area as it goes away to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Southee to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball full outside off, sticks his bat out and delicately played towards the off side. Takes the top edge, however, and goes past the diving keeper's right. Work for Boult in the deep
Commentary_short: Southee to Sarfraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: slower ball full outside off, pokes at the ball and runs it down to wide third man
Commentary_short: Southee to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, big stride forward and swept over square leg. Sarfraz slipped while playing that, but so did Tom Bruce at fine leg while trying to field. Fortunately, for the fielder, he managed to keep it inside the ropes
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, 3 runs

Commentary: sees the batsman come down the ground and darted full and wide outside off. The tall batsman manages to stretch out and get some bat to ball. Bunted to cover
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full outside leg stump, comes down the wicket and smacked past the bowler to long on. Couldn't get under that ball
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off stump, stays tall on the back foot and pulled to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: Taken? Yes! full and wide outside off, forces the batsman to reach at it once more, but Fakhar slaps it over point anyway. Man in the deep though, and it's an excellent catch from the outfielder. Dives forward and completes a tough low catch. Those dismissals are always difficult for the fielder to execute. Full marks. Small delay as the umpire wants to check if the catch was completed. Looks like Bruce's palms, ball in hand, hit the ground while trying to complete that catch. Were his fingers under the ball? Nothing conclusive on the replays. The on-field umpire's decision stands. Fakhar falls for 46.
Commentary_short: Santner to Fakhar Zaman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Fakhar Zaman c Bruce b Santner 46 (36b 5x4 1x6) SR: 127.77

Commentary: full on leg stump with Sarfraz taking a wide stance. Driven down the ground to long off
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, nudged off the back foot to deep backward square
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling across the batsman and punched to the deep on the off side
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: too short outside off, soars over the batsman's head as he comes dancing down the ground. Simple decision for the square-leg umpire
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 wide

Commentary: brave, and rides his luck! Good length outside off, and Sarfraz tries to heave it towards cover. Takes a thick edge, and goes over the keeper's head
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, slower ball on middle stump, Pulled along the ground behind square to fine leg
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, pulled by Haris to deep midwicket. Calls early for the second run
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Haris Sohail, 2 runs

Commentary: slower ball on a good length, and it's been punished! Stands tall and thumps his pull shot between deep midwicket and the man at cow corner. Threaded that shot beautifully
Commentary_short: de Grandhomme to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, backs away and cuts to point. The shot isn't directed well, and goes straight to Guptill
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, slapped off the back foot to the man in the deep on the offside
Commentary_short: Santner to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, tries to paddle sweep towards the leg side, but misses. Hits his pads, but impact was outside leg
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: darted full on middle stump after seeing the batsman back away. Bunted to cover off the front foot
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: Santner wins the battle! Tossed up full outside off, and tries to heave this over cover. Comes down the ground but the shot takes the top edge. It's a skyer, and pouched by short third man
Commentary_short: Santner to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sarfraz Ahmed c Sodhi b Santner 29 (21b 3x4 0x6) SR: 138.09

Commentary: full on off stump, driven off the front foot to cover, but no run there
Commentary_short: Santner to Umar Amin, no run

Commentary: slower ball, but short outside off. Boult misses his length, and it's been slapped over cover! Hit well, and beats both deep point and long off
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, going down the leg side and the batsman flicks it through to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, played off the back foot with soft hands. Nudged to point for a quick run
Commentary_short: Boult to Umar Amin, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, pulled emphatically to midwicket, but dropped by Sodhi! Went in cleanly, but popped out of Sodhi's hands as his knees hit the ground. Unlucky!
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, but angling down the leg side. Terrific stop by the keeper
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, 1 wide

Commentary: back of a length outside off, the batsman goes towards the leg side to make some extra room, and muscled over mid off! Struck powerfully
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: short on off stump, takes his eyes off the ball while trying to pull, but gets enough wood behind thats shot. Goes to deep backward square, and Haris keeps strike
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: thick top edge, but falls safe. Short of short third man. Full ball on middle stump for which the batsman came down the ground. Tried to slog this towards the leg side, but the spin induces the edge
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: short on middle stump, rocks back onto the back foot and pulls over deep backward square. Does it have the distance? You bet! The fielder's a spectator
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Umar Amin, SIX runs

Commentary: another drop! What is happening here. CDG the guilty party this time. Short on middle and pulled down the ground off the back foot. Off the bat's toe end and de Grandhomme fluffs this while running in
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Umar Amin, 2 runs

Commentary: punished! Full on off stump, and it's smacked over the non-striker's head. Trent Boult, at mid off, sticks his left hand out as the ball, but can't catch the ball. Goes beyond the boundary
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Umar Amin, SIX runs

Commentary: thumped! Full on middle and leg, comes down the ground and flicks this over deep midwicket on this occasion. Great use of the wrists
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Umar Amin, SIX runs

Commentary: the bowler has the last laugh, though! Flat, full and wide outside off. Forces the left-hander to stretch, who drags his slog to mid on. De Grandhomme redeems himself after that dropped catch
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Umar Amin, OUT
Dismissal_text: Umar Amin c de Grandhomme b Sodhi 21 (7b 0x4 3x6) SR: 300.00

Commentary: back of a length outside off, pulled along the carpet to deep backward square. Only a single
Commentary_short: Boult to Faheem Ashraf, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, swivels and pulls over square leg. No one in the deep there, as the ball goes a couple of bounces and into the boundary
Commentary_short: Boult to Faheem Ashraf, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker on leg stump, hits his boots as the ball goes down to fine leg. Terrific stop from the fielder in the deep. The dive saves the boundary, but the umpire thinks it came off the bat. Goes down as runs
Commentary_short: Boult to Faheem Ashraf, 2 runs

Commentary: full and quick! Tough to put those away. Yorker on middle and leg, and it crashes into his pads, before ricocheting onto off stump. A fiery delivery
Commentary_short: Boult to Faheem Ashraf, OUT

Commentary: full toss on off stump, opens the bat's face and runs it down to deep point
Commentary_short: Boult to Aamer Yamin, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, gets his front foot out of the way and slogs through the ball's line. But hit straight to midwicket
Commentary_short: Boult to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: starts off with a yorker that lands beyond leg stump. Takes his boot as the ball goes down the leg side. Terrific diving effort from the keeper
Commentary_short: Southee to Aamer Yamin, 1 leg bye

Commentary: full toss wide outside off, safe delivery to bowl with the batsmen looking to back away. Slapped to the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Southee to Haris Sohail, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and off, smacked over the non-striker's head to long on. Well intercepted by Guptill
Commentary_short: Southee to Aamer Yamin, 2 runs

Commentary: yorker on middle stump, squeezed away to cow corner. The ball reaches the deep very slowly, and allows them to come back for the second
Commentary_short: Southee to Aamer Yamin, 2 runs

Commentary: dropped, and it's gone for a boundary! Low full toss on leg stump, clipped off his pads to the man in the deep. Bruce gets under it, but the ball pops out of his hands again. Tries to turn around the parry the ball back, but his body hit the ropes while trying to do so. Bruce signalled that it's a boundary
Commentary_short: Southee to Aamer Yamin, FOUR runs

Commentary: finishes with a six! Full on middle stump, and muscled over the non-striker! Got under the ball and sends it into the stands. The Pakistan fans in the crowd are delighted with that! A shame that he dropped the crowd catch. Pakistan finish on 181 for 6
Commentary_short: Southee to Aamer Yamin, SIX runs

Commentary: full ball nips back in from middle stump, tapped to mid on
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Guptill, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, flicked off his toes to midwicket. No run
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Williamson, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, clipped to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Williamson, 1 run

Commentary: slips on his followthrough! Back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot to long on
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Guptill, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, slower ball this time and KW is deceived. Tries to defend it towards cover but inside edge hits his body instead
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Williamson, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, angling into the batsman, and clipped off his pads to midwicket
Commentary_short: Aamer Yamin to Guptill, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, punched off the back foot to mid on for a quick run
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Guptill, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, flicked off his hips past short fine leg. The fielder's giving it a chase, but there's no way he can catch up
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Williamson, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle and leg, stands tall and defends back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Williamson, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, punched off the back foot to mid off. Came down the wicket on this occasion
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Williamson, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot to cover. Can't pierce the infield
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Williamson, no run

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, tries to pull but can't make the contact. Hits his body instead
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Williamson, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, angling away from the right hander, and it's punched to cover. Can't go past the infield though
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Guptill, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, played with soft hands as he turns it off his hips to square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Guptill, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle and off, tapped to point for a quick run but it's a dangerous run! Direct hit and Williamson was gone, but the throw goes just over the top of the stumps. Amir could've been quicker to get back to the stumps, though
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Williamson, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, pulled rather unconvincingly off the back foot but has enough muscle behind that shot. Soars over the deep backward square boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Guptill, SIX runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, backs away and slashes at it, but only to point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Guptill, no run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, opens the bat's face with the delivery angling across him. Goes through to backward point

Commentary: what's going on? Confusion all around. Full outside leg and it's a terrific yorker that he can't put away. The ball goes between both legs and through to the keeper. Sarfraz throws at the stumps at the non-striker's because the batsmen were contemplating running across. Amir thinks he's got his man: not with the run out, but with the caught behind. They've taken the review. And yes, Amir is right. The ball hit the bat before going through his legs. Brings an end to the cameo. Taylor tells his partner, 'I didn't hit it, I promise', before walking out. Interesting, but the replays showed a spike on the snicko
